svg.text: OBReadStatement2
Data
Provides further details on a statement resource. Statement

Type: string MinLength: 1 MaxLength: 40 Description: A unique and immutable identifier used to identify the account resource. This identifier has no meaning to the account owner.
AccountId [1..1]

Type: string Format: date-time Description: Date and time at which the resource was created.All dates in the JSON payloads are represented in ISO 8601 date-time format. All date-time fields in responses must include the timezone. An example is below: 2017-04-05T10:43:07+00:00
CreationDateTime [1..1]

Type: string Format: date-time Description: Date and time at which the statement period ends.All dates in the JSON payloads are represented in ISO 8601 date-time format. All date-time fields in responses must include the timezone. An example is below: 2017-04-05T10:43:07+00:00
EndDateTime [1..1]

Type: string Format: date-time Description: Date and time at which the statement period starts.All dates in the JSON payloads are represented in ISO 8601 date-time format. All date-time fields in responses must include the timezone. An example is below: 2017-04-05T10:43:07+00:00
StartDateTime [1..1]

Type: string MinLength: 1 MaxLength: 500 Description: Other descriptions that may be available for the statement resource.
StatementDescription [0..*]

Type: string MinLength: 1 MaxLength: 40 Description: Unique identifier for the statement resource within an servicing institution. This identifier is both unique and immutable.
StatementId [0..1]

Type: string MinLength: 1 MaxLength: 35 Description: Unique reference for the statement. This reference may be optionally populated if available.
StatementReference [0..1]

Type: string Description: Statement type, in a coded form. Values: - AccountClosure - AccountOpening - Annual - Interim - RegularPeriodic
Type [1..1]
Set of elements used to provide details of a generic amount for the statement resource. StatementAmount

Type: string Description: Indicates whether the amount is a credit or a debit. Usage: A zero amount is considered to be a credit amount. Values: - Credit - Debit
CreditDebitIndicator [1..1]

Type: string Description: Amount type, in a coded form. Values: - UK.OBIE.ArrearsClosingBalance - UK.OBIE.AvailableBalance - UK.OBIE.AverageBalanceWhenInCredit - UK.OBIE.AverageBalanceWhenInDebit - UK.OBIE.AverageDailyBalance - UK.OBIE.BalanceTransferClosingBalance - UK.OBIE.CashClosingBalance - UK.OBIE.ClosingBalance - UK.OBIE.CreditLimit - UK.OBIE.CurrentPayment - UK.OBIE.DirectDebitPaymentDue - UK.OBIE.FSCSInsurance - UK.OBIE.MinimumPaymentDue - UK.OBIE.PendingTransactionsBalance - UK.OBIE.PreviousClosingBalance - UK.OBIE.PreviousPayment - UK.OBIE.PurchaseClosingBalance - UK.OBIE.StartingBalance - UK.OBIE.TotalAdjustments - UK.OBIE.TotalCashAdvances - UK.OBIE.TotalCharges - UK.OBIE.TotalCredits - UK.OBIE.TotalDebits - UK.OBIE.TotalPurchases
Type [1..1]
Amount of money associated with the amount type. Amount

Type: string Description: A number of monetary units specified in an active currency where the unit of currency is explicit and compliant with ISO 4217. Pattern: ^\d{1,13}$|^\d{1,13}\.\d{1,5}$
Amount [1..1]

Type: string Description: A code allocated to a currency by a Maintenance Agency under an international identification scheme, as described in the latest edition of the international standard ISO 4217 "Codes for the representation of currencies and funds". Pattern: ^[A-Z]{3,3}$
Currency [1..1]
Set of elements used to provide details of a benefit or reward amount for the statement resource. StatementBenefit

Type: string Description: Benefit type, in a coded form. Values: - UK.OBIE.Cashback - UK.OBIE.Insurance - UK.OBIE.TravelDiscount - UK.OBIE.TravelInsurance
Type [1..1]
Amount of money associated with the statement benefit type. Amount

Type: string Description: A number of monetary units specified in an active currency where the unit of currency is explicit and compliant with ISO 4217. Pattern: ^\d{1,13}$|^\d{1,13}\.\d{1,5}$
Amount [1..1]

Type: string Description: A code allocated to a currency by a Maintenance Agency under an international identification scheme, as described in the latest edition of the international standard ISO 4217 "Codes for the representation of currencies and funds". Pattern: ^[A-Z]{3,3}$
Currency [1..1]
Set of elements used to provide details of a generic date time for the statement resource. StatementDateTime

Type: string Format: date-time Description: Date and time associated with the date time type.All dates in the JSON payloads are represented in ISO 8601 date-time format. All date-time fields in responses must include the timezone. An example is below: 2017-04-05T10:43:07+00:00
DateTime [1..1]

Type: string Description: Date time type, in a coded form. Values: - UK.OBIE.BalanceTransferPromoEnd - UK.OBIE.DirectDebitDue - UK.OBIE.LastPayment - UK.OBIE.LastStatement - UK.OBIE.NextStatement - UK.OBIE.PaymentDue - UK.OBIE.PurchasePromoEnd - UK.OBIE.StatementAvailable
Type [1..1]
Set of elements used to provide details of a fee for the statement resource. StatementFee

Type: string Description: Indicates whether the amount is a credit or a debit. Usage: A zero amount is considered to be a credit amount. Values: - Credit - Debit
CreditDebitIndicator [1..1]

Type: string MinLength: 1 MaxLength: 128 Description: Description that may be available for the statement fee.
Description [0..1]

Type: string Description: How frequently the fee is applied to the Account. Values: - UK.OBIE.ChargingPeriod - UK.OBIE.PerTransactionAmount - UK.OBIE.PerTransactionPercentage - UK.OBIE.Quarterly - UK.OBIE.StatementMonthly - UK.OBIE.Weekly
Frequency [0..1]

Type: number Description: Rate charged for Statement Fee (where it is charged in terms of a rate rather than an amount)
Rate [0..1]

Type: string Description: Description that may be available for the statement fee rate type. Values: - UK.OBIE.AER - UK.OBIE.EAR
RateType [0..1]

Type: string Description: Fee type, in a coded form. Values: - UK.OBIE.Annual - UK.OBIE.BalanceTransfer - UK.OBIE.CashAdvance - UK.OBIE.CashTransaction - UK.OBIE.ForeignCashTransaction - UK.OBIE.ForeignTransaction - UK.OBIE.Gambling - UK.OBIE.LatePayment - UK.OBIE.MoneyTransfer - UK.OBIE.Monthly - UK.OBIE.Overlimit - UK.OBIE.PostalOrder - UK.OBIE.PrizeEntry - UK.OBIE.StatementCopy - UK.OBIE.Total
Type [1..1]
Amount of money associated with the statement fee type. Amount

Type: string Description: A number of monetary units specified in an active currency where the unit of currency is explicit and compliant with ISO 4217. Pattern: ^\d{1,13}$|^\d{1,13}\.\d{1,5}$
Amount [1..1]

Type: string Description: A code allocated to a currency by a Maintenance Agency under an international identification scheme, as described in the latest edition of the international standard ISO 4217 "Codes for the representation of currencies and funds". Pattern: ^[A-Z]{3,3}$
Currency [1..1]
Set of elements used to provide details of a generic interest amount related to the statement resource. StatementInterest

Type: string Description: Indicates whether the amount is a credit or a debit. Usage: A zero amount is considered to be a credit amount. Values: - Credit - Debit
CreditDebitIndicator [1..1]

Type: string MinLength: 1 MaxLength: 128 Description: Description that may be available for the statement interest.
Description [0..1]

Type: string Description: Specifies the statement fee type requested Values: - UK.OBIE.Daily - UK.OBIE.HalfYearly - UK.OBIE.Monthly - UK.OBIE.PerStatementDate - UK.OBIE.Quarterly - UK.OBIE.Weekly - UK.OBIE.Yearly
Frequency [0..1]

Type: number Description: field representing a percentage (e.g. 0.05 represents 5% and 0.9525 represents 95.25%). Note the number of decimal places may vary.
Rate [0..1]

Type: string Description: Description that may be available for the statement Interest rate type. Values: - UK.OBIE.BOEBaseRate - UK.OBIE.FixedRate - UK.OBIE.Gross - UK.OBIE.LoanProviderBaseRate - UK.OBIE.Net
RateType [0..1]

Type: string Description: Interest amount type, in a coded form. Values: - UK.OBIE.BalanceTransfer - UK.OBIE.Cash - UK.OBIE.EstimatedNext - UK.OBIE.Purchase - UK.OBIE.Total
Type [1..1]
Amount of money associated with the statement interest amount type. Amount

Type: string Description: A number of monetary units specified in an active currency where the unit of currency is explicit and compliant with ISO 4217. Pattern: ^\d{1,13}$|^\d{1,13}\.\d{1,5}$
Amount [1..1]

Type: string Description: A code allocated to a currency by a Maintenance Agency under an international identification scheme, as described in the latest edition of the international standard ISO 4217 "Codes for the representation of currencies and funds". Pattern: ^[A-Z]{3,3}$
Currency [1..1]
Set of elements used to provide details of a generic rate related to the statement resource. StatementRate

Type: string Description: Rate associated with the statement rate type. Pattern: ^(-?\d{1,3}){1}(\.\d{1,4}){0,1}$
Rate [1..1]

Type: string Description: Statement rate type, in a coded form. Values: - UK.OBIE.AnnualBalanceTransfer - UK.OBIE.AnnualBalanceTransferAfterPromo - UK.OBIE.AnnualBalanceTransferPromo - UK.OBIE.AnnualCash - UK.OBIE.AnnualPurchase - UK.OBIE.AnnualPurchaseAfterPromo - UK.OBIE.AnnualPurchasePromo - UK.OBIE.MonthlyBalanceTransfer - UK.OBIE.MonthlyCash - UK.OBIE.MonthlyPurchase
Type [1..1]
Set of elements used to provide details of a generic number value related to the statement resource. StatementValue

Type: string Description: Statement value type, in a coded form. Values: - UK.OBIE.AirMilesPoints - UK.OBIE.AirMilesPointsBalance - UK.OBIE.Credits - UK.OBIE.Debits - UK.OBIE.HotelPoints - UK.OBIE.HotelPointsBalance - UK.OBIE.RetailShoppingPoints - UK.OBIE.RetailShoppingPointsBalance
Type [1..1]

Type: string MinLength: 1 MaxLength: 40 Description: Value associated with the statement value type.
Value [1..1]
